% spi_1lane_stream.nw -- 1-lane QUADSPI stream wall-rate validation.
%
% Lives as a sibling chapter to src/spi.nw. The parent Makefile auto-
% discovers it via CHAPTERS := $(notdir $(basename $(wildcard src/*.nw)))
% and applies CHAP_RULES so a build/spi_1lane_stream/ tree is created
% without any parent-Makefile changes.

== 1-lane stream wall-rate chapter

This chapter scopes the 1-lane (LANES=1) QUADSPI stream-mode wall-rate
sweep so the mission-critical >=100 Mbps measurement runs in isolation
from the larger 1-lane regression in `src/spi.nw`. The mission target
is sustained FPGA->MP135 stream transfer of at least 100 Mbps in
1-lane mode with no data errors. The bitstream is `spi_1lane.bin`,
built by the spi chapter as a side effect of `make -C build/spi
bitstreams`; no new RTL is introduced here.

The chapter tests three prescaler settings using the auto-consume
streaming command (`A`), routed through `cmd_auto_stream` (cli.c:1236)
-> `stream_direct_crc_eligible(quad=0, raw=1) && auto_consume` ->
`stream_direct_crc_read` -> `qspi_mdma_crc_read` (qspi.c:790). This is
a DIFFERENT mechanism than `b` (which BLOCKED at spi block 8 due to
SB_IO timing margin at presc=15): `A` uses hardware MDMA + hardware
CRC1 drain through DMA, while `b` uses CPU-polled FIFO byte-by-byte.
The 1-lane peripheral raw read at presc=5 sshift=1 (`j 512 0`)
already PASSED on this rig in spi block 4, confirming the SCLK
~109 MHz sample point CAN land in the data eye for that
prescaler/sshift combo.

A preflight raw read at presc=203 (`j 512 0`) runs first to prove
the `spi_1lane.bin` bitstream is loaded and that the 1-lane data-phase
reaches the MP135 with the expected incrementing byte pattern. The
remaining four blocks order cheap controls first with the mission
target (`presc=5` >=100 Mbps wall rate over 32 MiB) last. Presc=15
(SB_IO margin failure, BLOCKED in spi block 8) and presc=255
(no diagnostic value) are intentionally skipped; the 512 MB stream
block is deferred to a later iteration if the mission target passes.

